tion" width="360" height="277" /></div>\r\n<div class="imagewidth50"><img class="alignnone" title="Call us for termite inspection, control &amp; prevention" src="http://localhost/allridspestcontrol/wp-content/themes/allrid/images/termite damage inside house.jpg" alt="Termite infestation " width="360" height="277" /></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWe use best products &amp; systems available in the market for termite management solution.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost/allridspestcontrol/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Altis_Reticulation_System_Brochure.pdf" target="_blank">Altis Reticulation System Brochure</a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost/allridspestcontrol/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Exterra-Brochure.pdf" target="_blank">Exterra Termite Management Brochure</a>\r\n<div style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://localhost/allridspestcontrol/wp-content/themes/allrid/images/brand.png" alt="" /></div>', 'Termite Pest management', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '445-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-08-26 12:54:24', '2015-08-26 12:54:24', '', 445, 'http://localhost/allridspestcontrol/445-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(582, 1, '2015-08-27 00:49:36', '2015-08-27 00:49:36', '<div class="page_description_first">\r\n<div class="page_header">\r\n<h1 style="text-align: justify;">Call us to control ticks                       PH:  02 8809 7945, M: 0414 467 981</h1>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>100% satisfaction</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Reliable on time &amp; honest service.</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Committed to leave your home exactly the way we found it.</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>People, pet and environmentally friendly</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div class="page_description_first">Ticks may cause the death of warm blooded animals by introducing toxins into the bloodstream, or cause non – fatal infections. There are many species of ticks, and their identification is usually a task for the specialist.</div>\r\n<div class="page_description_second">\r\n<div class="first_container">The brown dog tick, <em>Rhipicephalus sanguineus</em>, is an introduced species that has become established in Queensland and northern New South Wales.  In these areas, it is the usual tick on dogs, but it can also be found on cats, sheep, cattle, horses and humans.   In Queensland, it is blames for transmitting ‘Q Fever’ a typhus disease.\r\nThe Australian paralysis tick is often encountered on animals, distributed mainly along the eastern coast of Australia.  The species seems to be most abundant on the coastal plain.As a result of the presence of the paralysis tick, poisoning kills many domestic animals, particularly cats and dogs,\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="second_container"><img title="Ticks" src="http://localhost/allridspestcontrol/wp-content/themes/allrid/images/pest-control-ticks.jpg" alt="Pest contol ticks - Get rid of ticks" />\r\nTicks</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="page_description_first">as well as causing death to humans.  Humans showing tick-poisoning system should be referred to a doctor and, for animal’s sufferings from tick poisoning, the services of a veterinary surgeon should be enlisted.</div>\r\n<em>**Reference source: Urban Pest Management in Australia 5th edition</em>', 'Ticks', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'ticks', '', '', '2015-09-21 11:42:37', '2015-09-21 11:42:37', '', 0, 'http://localhost/allridspestcontrol/?post_type=pest-control&#038;p=582', 7, 'pest-control', '', 0),
(583, 1, '2015-08-27 00:49:36', '2015-08-27 00:49:36', '<div class="page_description_first">Ticks may cause the death of warm blooded animals by introducing toxins into the bloodstream, or cause non – fatal infections. There are many species of ticks, and their identification is usually a task for the specialist.</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="page_description_second">\r\n<div class="first_container">\r\nThe brown dog tick, <em>Rhipicephalus sanguineus</em>, is an introduced species that has become established in Queensland and northern New South Wales.  In these areas, it is the usual tick on dogs, but it can also be found on cats, sheep, cattle, horses and humans.   In Queensland, it is blames for transmitting ‘Q Fever’ a typhus disease.\r\n</br>The Australian paralysis tick is often encountered on animals, distributed mainly along the eastern coast of Australia.  The species seems to be most abundant on the coastal plain.<br/>\r\nAs a result of the presence of the paralysis tick, poisoning kills many domestic animals, particularly cats and dogs,\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="second_container">\r\n	<img title="Ticks" alt="Pest contol ticks - Get rid of ticks" src="http://localhost/allridspestcontrol/wp-content/themes/allrid/images/pest-control-ticks.jpg"><figcaption>Ticks</figcaption>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="page_description_first">\r\n  as well as causing death to humans.  Humans showing tick-poisoning system should be referred to a doctor and, for animal’s sufferings from tick poisoning, the services of a veterinary surgeon should be enlisted.</div>\r\n<em>**Reference source: Urban Pest Management in Australia 5th edition</em>', 'Ticks', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '582-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-08-27 00:49:36', '2015-08-27 00:49:36', '', 582, 'http://localhost/allridspestcontrol/582-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
