les die off, and the newly fertilised queens hibernate to build other nests the following year.  The new queen lays eggs in the cells of the nest, and after some weeks in the larval stage the wasps pupate and emerge as adults, which take over the work of the nest.</br></br>After one summer, the nest may have 10,000 individuals.</div>\r\n<div class="second_container"><img title="Eauropean Wasps" src="http://localhost/allridspestcontrol/wp-content/themes/allrid/images/wasps-removal.png" alt="Pest removal - Get rid of wasps" />\r\nEuropean Wasps</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<em>**Reference source: Urban Pest Management in Australia 5th edition</em>', 'Wasps', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '585-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-08-27 00:52:25', '2015-08-27 00:52:25', '', 585, 'http://localhost/allridspestcontrol/585-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
