ed-back Spider" src="http://localhost/allridspestcontrol/wp-content/themes/allrid/images/Redback_spider.jpg" alt="Spider Control - Redback spider removal" width="218" height="258" /> Red-back Spider[/caption]\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="page_description_second">\r\n<div class="title">MOUSE SPIDER</div>\r\n<div class="first_container">Females often mistaken for Funnelwebs. Large glossy black bodied spider, with the male having a red forepart of the cephalothorax. Female lives in holes with double doors in the ground. Has blunted spinnerets and strong jaws. Toxic and painful bite.</div>\r\n<div class="second_container">\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="256"]<img title="Mouse Spider" src="http://localhost/allridspestcontrol/wp-content/themes/allrid/images/spider-control-mouse-spider.jpg" alt="Spider Control - Remove mouse spider" width="256" height="223" /> Mouse Spider[/caption]\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="page_description_second">\r\n<div class="title">WHITE TAILED SPIDER</div>\r\n<div class="first_container">A small dark brown spider with a characteristic white spot on the end of the abdomen. Usually encountered inside houses sheltering from the weather or introduced on clothing brought in from the clothes line. Bite is not usually painful, though may become very painful at a later stage. Ulcers may develop to a stage where necrosis of the skin occurs.</div>\r\n<div class="second_container">\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="239"]<img title="White Tailed Spider" src="http://localhost/allridspestcontrol/wp-content/themes/allrid/images/spider-control-white-tailed-spider.jpg" alt="Spider Control - Remove white tailed spider" width="239" height="282" /> White Tailed Spider[/caption]\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="page_description_second">\r\n<div class="title">BLACK HOUSE SPIDER</div>\r\n<div class="first_container">Both sexes are dark brown to grey/black with body markings. Builds webs in dark corners of windows,